New world screwworm (_Cochliomyia hominivorax_), Panama
-------------------------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 16 Aug 2022
Confirmed: 16 Aug 2022
Reported: 6 Sep 2022
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 4 Aug 2022
Causal agent: _Cochliomyia hominivorax_
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location 1: Pigandi Grande, Kuna de Madungandi, Chepo, Panama
Started: 16 Aug 2022
Epidemiological unit: farm

Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Birds / 307 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Equidae / 28 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Swine / 36 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Goats / 50 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Cattle / 442 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: The population described is the total population in the farms located within a 5 km radius around the outbreak. The birds are backyard hens for self-consumption.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: movement of the causal agent from another nearby outbreak.

Epidemiological comments: Since [22 Jul 2022], measures including release of sterile insects in the field have been implemented in 2 points, 9.5 liters of insects (approximately), weekly; this measure will be maintained for a period equal to 3 biological cycles of the agent from the last case detected [16 Aug 2022]. Aerial release of sterile insects, by means of 2 weekly flights, at a dose of 3000 flies per linear nautical mile [1.85 km]. Specific epidemiological surveillance was carried out in all farms within a 5 km radius around Pigand√≠ Grande case, without any other finding. Routine surveillance, health education campaigns (for local people, producers, technicians, among others) and release measures will be maintained for a period of three 3 biological cycles (9 weeks).

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures: surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; treatment; movement control; disinfestation

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Outbreaks / Test / Test date / Result
Comision Panama-Estados Unidos para la Erradicacion y Prevencion del Gusano Barrenador (CoPEG) [Panama-USA Commission for the Eradication and Prevention of Screwworms] national laboratory / Equidae / 1 / Parasitological examination / 16 Aug 2022 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the WOAH report at the source URL above.]

